text: Sesam was a Scandinavian internet search engine. Sesam, SESAM or SeSaM may also refer to: * SESAM (FEM), a structural analysis software * SESAM (database), a relational database developed by Fujitsu Siemens * Semiconductor saturable-absorber mirror, a component used in some lasers * SeSaM, a molecular biology method for diversity creation by random mutagenesis ==See also== * Sesame, a flowering plant used as a seed crop * Sesame (disambiguation) * Various wild and cultivated plants in the genus Sesamum
title: Sesam (disambiguation)
